  "texts": [
    "For every formal Lipschitz sum i (g i, κ i), there exists a regular formalLipschitz sum i (f i, π i) ∼ i (g i, κ i).",
    "If (f i, π i) is regular, then s( i (f i, π i)) = i L d i.Proof.",
    "The latter statement follows immediately from the definitions.",
    "For the former statement, suppose i (g i, κ i) is a formal Lipschitz sum.",
    "Let I 0 ⊂ N stand for the set of those indices, for whichT (g i, κ i) = 0 for every T ∈ P d ([0, 1] d)."
  ]
